        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Order for supplies</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><persName>Department of State</persName> <placeName>Colombia </placeName><date when="1836-11-19">Nov. 19th- 1836</date>&#8212;</p>

<p>Messrs <persName>Toby </persName>and <persName>Brother</persName>. <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>,</p>

<p><persName>Gentlemen</persName>,</p>

<p>There are various little articles, which are indispensable in the <persName>Offices
of the different Departments</persName>, and the impossibility of obtaining them here
is my apology for troubling you with them. You would oblige me by
procuring such as are enumerated in the subjoined list, and having them
directed to the <placeName>Department of State, Columbia</placeName>. An early attention to this
request will relieve the <persName>Government </persName>from much inconvenience.</p>

<p><persName>S. F. Austin Sec of State</persName></p>

<p>1. Letter Book  </p>

<p>1. Record D°-  </p>

<p>1. Register	 </p>

<p>These 3 large and well Lettered on the Back. Letter Book <persName>Department of State</persName> etc. etc. ruled, but not crossed, longitudinally&#8212;</p>

<p>4 Blank books  Lettered <persName>Department of State</persName></p>

<p>1/2 doz. small blank books for mem. accts. etc.</p>

<p>2	Reams of superfine light blue letter paper.</p>

<p>4 Ditto " " foolscap&#8212;</p>

<p>Sealing Wax and wafers, a	good supply Black lead pencils and quills&#8212;</p>

<p>3	Cards of best quality steel	pens&#8212;</p>

<p>Stamp with a star in it</p>

<p>4	Large inkstands.</p>

<p>1/2 Doz. vials, red ink.</p>

<p>6 Bottles, black ink.</p>

<p>1/2 doz. papers, ink powder.</p>

<p>2	Ivory folders.</p>

<p>1/2 Doz. red tape.</p>

<p>3	Penknives.</p>

<p>3	Round rulers.</p>

<p>4	Sandboxes and a good supply of sand.</p>

<p>6 Candlesticks, brass, with large bottoms.<pb n="457"/></p>

<p>4 Snuffers.</p>

<p>1 Box of candles.</p>

<p>Regulations of the U. S. in relation to the four Departments of State, Treasury, War
and Navy.</p>

<p>Elliot's Diplomatic code&#8212;</p>

<p>Story on the Constitution of the United States</p>

<p>Kent's Commentaries.</p>

<p>Form Book, containing such forms as are used in the U. S. for Civil Commissions,
Credentials and other State Documents&#8212;Land Laws of the U. S.</p>

<p>2. Large trunks for the safety of the public archives&#8212;</p>

<p>1	Piece of green baize for table covers, etc.&#8212;</p>

<p>Silk and wrapping paper; convenient quantity of each&#8212;</p>

<p>Blotting paper etc.</p>

<p>2	Large Portfolios</p>

<p>Civil Code of Louisiana&#8212;</p>



        </div1>
